\begin_layout Section*
MUTTON BROTH.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Take 2 lbs.
 of scrag of mutton; to take the blood out, put it into a stew pan, and
 cover it with cold water; when the water becomes milk warm, pour it off,
 skim it well, then put it in again, with 4 or 5 pints of water, a teaspoonful
 of salt, a tablespoonful of best grits, and an onion; set it on a slow
