\begin_layout Standard
Cut the plant in April; boil the stalks in salt and water until tender;
 remove and drain it well; scrape the outside and dry it in a clean cloth,
 place it in a syrup and allow it to remain there 3 or 4 days, closely covered.
 The syrup must be made from the same weight of sugar that there is of fruit,
 allowing 1 pint water to 1 lb.
