 it out, and to a pint of this liquor take a pound of double-refined sugar
 boiled to sugar again; then put in your codlin liquor, boil it a little
 together as fast as you can; then put in your golden pippins, boil them
 up fast for a little while; just before the last boiling, squeeze in the
 juice of a lemon; boil it up quick once more; take care they do not lose
 colour; take the pippins out, and put them into the glasses with the jelly.
